column1: #Text=The Wrecking Crew music documentary hits cinemas
#Text=Music documentary The Wrecking Crew received its commercial première Friday , screening in cinemas in Los Angeles and New York via Magnolia Pictures .
#Text=Two decades in the making , Denny Tedesco 's documentary observes and honours a group of session musicians collectively known as " The Wrecking Crew " .

column1: #Text=Tedesco explained he was moved to begin the documentary when he learned his father , guitarist Tommy Tedesco , had cancer in 1996 .
#Text=" When they said he had a year to live — and I always wanted to do this story about The Wrecking Crew — my concern was , if I do n't do it , it 's going to be the biggest regret of my life " .
#Text=Tedesco commented on his anticipation of audiences ' reaction at Nuart Theatre in Los Angeles , " People say , ' are n't you tired of watching it ? '

column1: #Text=A Kickstarter campaign raised $ 300,000 , which paid for licensing and session artists .
#Text=Billboard reports the money was able to go towards the creation of outtakes for a future DVD .
#Text=Tedesco said he wanted to keep outtakes of the interviews he conducted that did n't make it into the movie .
#Text=" I want to do outtakes of every musician , a lot of whom are n't in the movie[ ... ]

column1: #Text=Aside from the interviews , the documentary also includes footage of The Wrecking Crew , filmed by Hal Blaine .
#Text=He dubbed himself a director as he joked around with the other musicians .
#Text=" I had a camera , and I took it to work and I became a director of sorts .
